Apologize if the link above isn't clickable - not a lot of time to edit stuff before I need to walk out the door.<br>
<br>
The guide on this site isn't bad for building a system that will handle everyday tasks and do well in gaming.  I would double the amount of system  RAM they recommend and go with the intel CPU for compatibility on your first PC.  I would also find, borrow, steal, a copy of Windows98 SE as the system's OS.  XP is just crap, period, when it comes to games.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that the prices they list are mostly for OEM components off of Pricewatch.com.  It's your responsibility to do some checking around before ordering anything from the listed sellers.  If you purchase the components in a retail store you will pay a higher price.  You'll also get a better warranty.<br>
<br>
As far as anything else on Sharky Extreme, I think the lead editor is a self-righteous arse who thinks reporting consist of nothing more than his personal opinions.  They also have this attitude that they can recommend hardware that is future proof.  No such thing in the PC industry.  Sharky may have cleaned up his act lately, haven't had a look in awhile.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
